{
  "texts": [
    "These methods align with global trends that promote hands-on, inquiry-based learning experiences to help educators understand and apply STEM knowledge in real-world contexts.",
    "Collaborative learning and reflection have also emerged as essential elements in improving teaching practices.",
    "Studies by Peng and Zhu (2020) and Li and Li (2023) show that collaborative projects and reflective practices can significantly enhance teachers' ability to integrate interdisciplinary content and address regional challenges.",
    "Moreover, the inclusion of technology-enhanced training and online platforms for teacher training is becoming increasingly relevant (Lin et al. 2023; Wu and Zhang, 2022).",
    "The analysis also highlights the impact of contextual factors on the success of these initiatives."
  ]
}